1) Operational guidelines for the implementation of new / revised employment promotion measures were completed and in full use by the National Employment Service;
2) Self-employment measure was operationalized in 2016. 75 youth were trained, and 38 new businesses registered;
3) Feasibility study on work-based learning models is on-going; and was proceeded by a study on incentives / disincentives for private sector participation in work-based learning; 
4) Skills Needs Assessment methodology being consulted with relevant stakeholders;
5) National list of occupations and occupational descriptions finalized and pending approval by the Council of Ministers.

1) The Government received continuous support in enhancing effectiveness, transparency and accountability of employment promotion measure, in particular in rural areas;
2) 2nd round of self-employment measure delivered with increasing engagement of government authorities to enable sustainability; 
3) Feasibility study on work-based learning models carried out
4) Quality frame for VET schools developed.
5) National list of occupations and occupational descriptions approved by the Council of Ministers
6) Skills Needs Analysis undertaken

1)	Assessment for the 2014-2015 ALMM programmes has been carried out; study on policy options for extending employment services to rural areas and measures to address rural employment initiated and on-going (to be completed in 2018);
2)	2nd round of self-employment delivered with 152 young people being trained and 51 young people receiving grants (30% were women);
3)	Feasibility study on work-based learning carried out, assessing the work-based learning models introduced and implemented among the VET providers in Albania in the last five years.
4)	The Programme has prepared a reference framework for quality for VET schools. It is a model depicting central dimensions of a good VET provider, which is meant to help understand and develop VET providers in Albania in a holistic manner. 
5)	National list of occupations and occupational descriptions approved by the Council of Ministers in September 2017
6)	Skills Needs Analysis conducted. The national enterprise survey covered a representative sample of 2560 enterprises from all sectors of economy (except for agriculture) to explore current needs in skilled labour force.

